author: slaws
msg: TUSCANY-2799 - don't return responses inside arrays. Generally reorg the code so that the message processors only worry about getting data in and out of JMS message while the interceptors worry about whether the data should be wrapped as an array. In this way the forward path can do array wrapping in order to keep databinding happy while the response path can omit array wrapping
This is an empty revision for padding.
